description.narrative: (Kenya): .Afya Timiza focuses on advancing the journey to self-reliance in Turkana and Samburu counties by strengthening systems and building local capacity for family planning, reproductive, maternal, newborn, child, adolescent health, and nutrition. Using FY 2019 funds, Afya Timiza will prioritize leadership, management competencies, good governance, sustainable financing efforts, and accountability to enhance capacity and commitment for development programs. Domestic resource mobilization efforts will aim at securing at least 26 percent of the annual county budget for health. For greater social accountability between communities and county governments, the activity will use UNICEF's Citizen Voice and Action process. Data use within a collaborating, learning, and adapting approach will help to improve planning. To increase enrollment in the National Hospital Insurance Fund (NHIF), a livestock based financing option will be developed. Accreditation of health service providers under NHIF will be expanded and advocacy for NHIF provision for community health volunteers as an incentive framework will begin. The activity will support integrated supply chain systems, develop health worker retention strategies, and support county and sub-county health team mentorship activities for service quality improvement. Integration with HIV for client-centered services to reach hard to reach populations will be conducted through outreach services. Community and health facility activities will expand prevention and case management of diarrhea and pneumonia, improve nutrition, and expand key social behavior change interventions. The activity will collaborate and coordinate with USAID partners through the Partnership for Resilience and Economic Growth. In strengthening the health systems and institutions in these vast semi arid- counties, the activity aligns with U.S. security objectives and demonstrates strong U.S. leadership and influence in Kenya's health sector...
